article.headline: Sacramento State 74, Denver 53
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Haron Hargrave scored 31 points to lift Sacramento State to a 74-53 win over Denver Friday night. Hargrave scored 23 of his points in the final 20 minutes as Sacramento State (2-2) overcame a first half deficit and limited Denver (0-3) to just 19 points in the second half. Hargrave shot 11-of-17 from the field, including 8-of-10 from 3-point range. Denver went on a 13-0 run to end the first half and take a 34-26 lead into the break, but Sacramento State quickly erased that deficient by starting the second half with a 10-0 run. Antonio Porch and Tyler Bullock led Denver with 11 points each. Loren Leath and Alex Baulsey scored 15 and 12 points, respectively, for Sacramento State.
